# Cline rules — kit integration
#
# Cline reads .clinerules from project root. Mirrors .cursorrules.

After any non-trivial edit batch, call the `kit_check` MCP tool
(category=security) and surface any `fail` results before continuing.
If the user asks to install a dependency, call `kit_triage` first.

Never bypass `kit_check` failures by skipping pre-commit hooks
(`--no-verify`) or by editing hook configuration without explicit
user approval.
